[1]
Date: Sat 29 Aug 2009
Source: WBT Insider, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
<http://www.wbt.com/news/details.cfm?article_id=47769>


Health officials are fanning out through a North Carolina
neighborhood, trying to stop a sudden outbreak of syphilis.

Officials in Forsyth County told the Winston-Salem Journal that the
140 cases of the sexually transmitted disease reported so far this
year [2009] is more than triple the cases reported in all of 2008.
About 125 officials and volunteers are spending Saturday [29 Aug 2009]
walking through a neighborhood where a cluster of cases have been
reported, offering free blood tests for syphilis and HIV. Anyone who
agrees to be tested will get a Wal-Mart gift card.

--
